  "sita-fire-ordeal": {
    "en": [
      "Sita and the Fire Ordeal is best understood within the storytelling traditions of India in South Asia. It stays anchored in hero, trial, and honor rather than in a single fixed version. It is most useful as a guide to the themes of hero, trial, and honor. That keeps the story tied to landscape, community, and transmission from the start.",
      "As an epic-facing entry, it gathers attention around hero, trial, and the kind of trial that tests standing or endurance. The emphasis falls on remembered scale, heroic pressure, and the path a community keeps worth retelling. Even where versions differ, the story usually persists because it carries honor, ordeal, and movement across a larger world. That larger frame matters more than pretending we already have every episode pinned down.",
      "Here Sita and the Fire Ordeal serves as a regional memory of what counts as greatness, burden, or costly achievement in India in South Asia. It also keeps the relation between hero, route, and audience in view. The motifs of hero, trial, and honor do the real structural work. What endures is the scale of the ordeal and the memory of who was judged equal to it."
    ],
    "zh": [
      "《悉多与火焰考验》最好先放回南亚的印度的讲述传统里来理解。这条叙述把重心落在“英雄”“试炼”和“荣誉”这些意象上，而不是单一固定版本上。它更适合被读作关于“英雄”“试炼”“荣誉”的地方讲述。因此开头就把地点、社群和传承方式一起摆了出来。",
      "如果把它放在史诗的尺度上看，视线自然会集中到“英雄”“试炼”和必须承受的试炼上。这类条目保存的往往是英雄压力、远行规模和社群愿意反复讲述的壮阔感。哪怕细节版本有差异，荣誉、磨难和行路通常仍是骨架。真正重要的是那种被记成“大事”的结构，而不是假装已经掌握全部桥段。",
      "因此《悉多与火焰考验》在这里保存的是南亚的印度关于伟业、重负与代价的记忆。它也让英雄、路线和听众之间的关系继续可见。支撑整条叙述的，其实是“英雄”“试炼”“荣誉”这些母题。最后被记住的，是试炼的尺度，以及谁被认为配得上承受它。"
    ]
  },
  "prahlada-narasimha": {
    "en": [
      "Prahlada and Narasimha is best understood within the storytelling traditions of India in South Asia. It stays anchored in ritual, balance, and offering rather than in a single fixed version. It is most useful as a guide to the themes of ritual, balance, and offering. That keeps the story tied to landscape, community, and transmission from the start.",
      "As a sacred story, it organizes memory around ritual, balance, and the duties or balances those images sustain. The point is not only what happened once, but how ritual language and inherited teaching keep the account active. In many traditions, that makes repetition, setting, and symbolic order just as important as dramatic sequence. The story therefore belongs to lived practice as much as to literary summary.",
      "Read this way, Prahlada and Narasimha keeps a religious pattern visible inside India in South Asia without forcing it into one compressed synopsis. It links devotion, place, and shared obligation in a way that remains legible even before deeper sourcing arrives. The themes of ritual, balance, and offering provide the durable frame. What is preserved above all is a way of holding order, offering, and reverence together."
    ],
    "zh": [
      "《普拉赫拉达与人狮》最好先放回南亚的印度的讲述传统里来理解。这条叙述把重心落在“仪式”“平衡”和“供奉”这些意象上，而不是单一固定版本上。它更适合被读作关于“仪式”“平衡”“供奉”的地方讲述。因此开头就把地点、社群和传承方式一起摆了出来。",
      "作为神圣故事，它会把“仪式”“平衡”和被维系的职责、供奉或平衡组织在一起。这类传统在意的往往不只是某件事曾经发生过，还包括它怎样在仪式和教诲里继续有效。因此重复、场所和象征秩序，常常和剧情推进一样重要。故事既属于叙述，也属于实践。",
      "从这个角度读，《普拉赫拉达与人狮》保存的是南亚的印度内部的一种宗教结构，而不是被压缩成一条剧情直线。它把信念、地点和共同义务继续拴在一起。“仪式”“平衡”“供奉”提供了这条叙述最稳定的框架。最后被保存下来的，是把秩序、供奉与敬畏维系在一起的方式。"
    ]
  },
  "shirin-farhad": {
    "en": [
      "Shirin and Farhad is best understood within the storytelling traditions of Iran in Western Asia. It stays anchored in wit, choice, and journey rather than in a single fixed version. It is most useful as a guide to the themes of wit, choice, and journey. That keeps the story tied to landscape, community, and transmission from the start.",
      "As a folktale, it leans on the tension between wit, choice, and the choices that make retellings memorable. The interest lies in how a teller would shape cunning, travel, warning, or reversal for a local audience. That means the story matters as oral craft as much as as a chain of named events. The line of transmission is part of the content, not just the container around it.",
      "Seen this way, Shirin and Farhad preserves a style of communal telling that belongs to Iran in Western Asia as much as to any one performer. It keeps attention on what listeners are asked to remember, repeat, and pass on. The motifs of wit and choice stay legible without forcing a fake adventure arc onto the page. What lasts is the telling pattern that lets the story travel from one voice to the next."
    ],
    "zh": [
      "《希琳与法尔哈德》最好先放回西亚的伊朗的讲述传统里来理解。这条叙述把重心落在“机智”“选择”和“旅程”这些意象上，而不是单一固定版本上。它更适合被读作关于“机智”“选择”“旅程”的地方讲述。因此开头就把地点、社群和传承方式一起摆了出来。",
      "放进民间故事的语境里，它真正有力的地方在于“机智”“选择”和人物选择如何被讲得好听、好记。这种故事常常靠机巧、转折、路途或教训在口耳之间留下来。所以它重要的不只是发生了什么，也包括讲述者怎样把它讲给本地听众。传承方式本身就是内容的一部分。",
      "从这个角度看，《希琳与法尔哈德》保存的是属于西亚的伊朗的讲法，而不只是一个被压扁的梗概。它让人注意哪些片段值得被记住、重复和继续转述。像“机智”与“选择”这样的母题仍然清楚，却不会再被硬套成假冒险。最后真正留下来的，是一套能从一个讲述者传到下一个讲述者的说法。"
    ]
  },
