  "kaveh-blacksmith": {
    "en": [
      "Kaveh the Blacksmith is best understood within the storytelling traditions of Iran in Western Asia. It stays anchored in memory, lineage, and place rather than in a single fixed version. It is most useful as a guide to the themes of memory, lineage, and place. That keeps the story tied to landscape, community, and transmission from the start.",
      "As legendary history, it is anchored in memory, lineage, and the memory of people or places treated as worth remembering together. The story matters because it helps a region describe lineage, rule, migration, conflict, or foundation in memorable form. That makes the overlap between history and storytelling part of the point, not a flaw to hide. The entry therefore keeps its attention on local remembrance rather than inventing a false canonical plot.",
      "In that sense, Kaveh the Blacksmith works as a memory-site for Iran in Western Asia, where names, locations, and inherited reputation stay bound together. It lets readers see how narrative helps organize public memory before archival precision is fully restored. The strongest through-lines remain memory, lineage, and place. What lasts is the form of remembrance itself and the public memory it helps a place keep."
    ],
    "zh": [
      "《铁匠卡维》最好先放回西亚的伊朗的讲述传统里来理解。这条叙述把重心落在“记忆”“血统”和“地点”这些意象上，而不是单一固定版本上。它更适合被读作关于“记忆”“血统”“地点”的地方讲述。因此开头就把地点、社群和传承方式一起摆了出来。",
      "当它被当作传奇历史来读时，核心就在“记忆”“血统”以及哪些人和地点值得一起被记住。这种故事的重要性，往往在于它帮助一个地区把血统、统治、迁徙、冲突或建城讲成可传的形式。历史和讲述在这里本来就交叠在一起，并不需要假装完全分开。所以这条 narrative 会先把注意力留在地方记忆本身，而不是编造一个唯一版本的剧情线。",
      "也因此，《铁匠卡维》更像西亚的伊朗的一处记忆节点，把名字、地点和声望系在一起。它让读者先看见叙事怎样帮助公共记忆成形。贯穿其中的仍然是“记忆”“血统”“地点”这些主轴。最后真正留下来的，是一种地方社会如何记住自己过去的方式。"
    ]
  },
