  "mahsuri-langkawi": {
    "en": [
      "Mahsuri of Langkawi is best understood within the storytelling traditions of Malaysia in Southeast Asia. It stays anchored in memory, lineage, and place rather than in a single fixed version. It is most useful as a guide to the themes of memory, lineage, and place. That keeps the story tied to landscape, community, and transmission from the start.",
      "As legendary history, it is anchored in memory, lineage, and the memory of people or places treated as worth remembering together. The story matters because it helps a region describe lineage, rule, migration, conflict, or foundation in memorable form. That makes the overlap between history and storytelling part of the point, not a flaw to hide. The entry therefore keeps its attention on local remembrance rather than inventing a false canonical plot.",
      "In that sense, Mahsuri of Langkawi works as a memory-site for Malaysia in Southeast Asia, where names, locations, and inherited reputation stay bound together. It lets readers see how narrative helps organize public memory before archival precision is fully restored. The strongest through-lines remain memory, lineage, and place. What lasts is the form of remembrance itself and the public memory it helps a place keep."
    ],
    "zh": [
      "《兰卡威的玛苏丽》最好先放回东南亚的马来西亚的讲述传统里来理解。这条叙述把重心落在“记忆”“血统”和“地点”这些意象上，而不是单一固定版本上。它更适合被读作关于“记忆”“血统”“地点”的地方讲述。因此开头就把地点、社群和传承方式一起摆了出来。",
      "当它被当作传奇历史来读时，核心就在“记忆”“血统”以及哪些人和地点值得一起被记住。这种故事的重要性，往往在于它帮助一个地区把血统、统治、迁徙、冲突或建城讲成可传的形式。历史和讲述在这里本来就交叠在一起，并不需要假装完全分开。所以这条 narrative 会先把注意力留在地方记忆本身，而不是编造一个唯一版本的剧情线。",
      "也因此，《兰卡威的玛苏丽》更像东南亚的马来西亚的一处记忆节点，把名字、地点和声望系在一起。它让读者先看见叙事怎样帮助公共记忆成形。贯穿其中的仍然是“记忆”“血统”“地点”这些主轴。最后真正留下来的，是一种地方社会如何记住自己过去的方式。"
    ]
  },
  "badang-strongman": {
    "en": [
      "Badang the Strongman is best understood within the storytelling traditions of Singapore in Southeast Asia. It stays anchored in wit, choice, and journey rather than in a single fixed version. It is most useful as a guide to the themes of wit, choice, and journey. That keeps the story tied to landscape, community, and transmission from the start.",
      "As a folktale, it leans on the tension between wit, choice, and the choices that make retellings memorable. The interest lies in how a teller would shape cunning, travel, warning, or reversal for a local audience. That means the story matters as oral craft as much as as a chain of named events. The line of transmission is part of the content, not just the container around it.",
      "Seen this way, Badang the Strongman preserves a style of communal telling that belongs to Singapore in Southeast Asia as much as to any one performer. It keeps attention on what listeners are asked to remember, repeat, and pass on. The motifs of wit and choice stay legible without forcing a fake adventure arc onto the page. What lasts is the telling pattern that lets the story travel from one voice to the next."
    ],
    "zh": [
      "《大力士巴当》最好先放回东南亚的新加坡的讲述传统里来理解。这条叙述把重心落在“机智”“选择”和“旅程”这些意象上，而不是单一固定版本上。它更适合被读作关于“机智”“选择”“旅程”的地方讲述。因此开头就把地点、社群和传承方式一起摆了出来。",
      "放进民间故事的语境里，它真正有力的地方在于“机智”“选择”和人物选择如何被讲得好听、好记。这种故事常常靠机巧、转折、路途或教训在口耳之间留下来。所以它重要的不只是发生了什么，也包括讲述者怎样把它讲给本地听众。传承方式本身就是内容的一部分。",
      "从这个角度看，《大力士巴当》保存的是属于东南亚的新加坡的讲法，而不只是一个被压扁的梗概。它让人注意哪些片段值得被记住、重复和继续转述。像“机智”与“选择”这样的母题仍然清楚，却不会再被硬套成假冒险。最后真正留下来的，是一套能从一个讲述者传到下一个讲述者的说法。"
    ]
  },
  "orpheus-eurydice-atlas": {
    "en": [
      "Orpheus and Eurydice is best understood within the storytelling traditions of Greece in Southern Europe. It stays anchored in origin, cosmos, and transformation rather than in a single fixed version. It is most useful as a guide to the themes of origin, cosmos, and transformation. That keeps the story tied to landscape, community, and transmission from the start.",
      "In mythic terms, the strongest pressure falls on how origin and cosmos explain beginnings, powers, or changes in the world. The title points less to one fixed episode than to a sacred pattern carried by repeated local telling. Details may vary from version to version, but the link between cosmos, place, and transformation remains central. Readers are meant to notice what kind of world this story imagines before they look for a scene-by-scene synopsis.",
      "As a result, Orpheus and Eurydice works here as a map of origin-thinking rather than as a single locked sequence of events. It keeps Greece in Southern Europe visible as more than backdrop, because the land itself helps hold the story's meaning. The memory carried forward is not only about gods or beings, but about how a region names order and change. What remains is a way of explaining why the world takes the shape it does."
    ],
    "zh": [
      "《俄耳甫斯与欧律狄刻》最好先放回南欧的希腊的讲述传统里来理解。这条叙述把重心落在“起源”“宇宙”和“变化”这些意象上，而不是单一固定版本上。它更适合被读作关于“起源”“宇宙”“变化”的地方讲述。因此开头就把地点、社群和传承方式一起摆了出来。",
      "放在神话类型里看，最重要的是“起源”与“宇宙”如何解释世界开端、力量来源或秩序变化。这个标题指向的未必是唯一固定的情节，而是一种会被反复讲述的神圣结构。即使不同版本的细节并不一样，宇宙、地貌和变化之间的关系通常不会消失。读者首先该把握的，是这则故事怎样想象世界，而不是硬找一条并不存在的统一剧情。",
      "所以《俄耳甫斯与欧律狄刻》在这里更像一张关于起源观念的地图，而不是被锁死成唯一版本的梗概。南欧的希腊也不只是背景，因为地貌本身就在帮助这则神话保存意义。被留下来的不只是神灵名字，还有地方如何命名秩序和变化的方式。最终留下来的，是一整套解释世界为何如此的说法。"
    ]
  },
