      "Finn and the Giant's Causeway is best understood within the storytelling traditions of Ireland in Northern Europe. It stays anchored in wit, choice, and journey rather than in a single fixed version. It is most useful as a guide to the themes of wit, choice, and journey. That keeps the story tied to landscape, community, and transmission from the start.",
