  "flying-dutchman": {
    "en": [
      "The Flying Dutchman is best understood within the storytelling traditions of Netherlands in Western Europe. It stays anchored in warning, boundary, and fear rather than in a single fixed version. It is most useful as a guide to the themes of warning, boundary, and fear. That keeps the story tied to landscape, community, and transmission from the start.",
      "As a creature legend, the story is strongest where warning, boundary, and fear define a zone of warning. The being matters because it makes a boundary feel inhabited, risky, or morally charged. Such tales often survive through repeated caution, not through one universally fixed storyline. That is why place and atmosphere matter as much as named action.",
      "The Flying Dutchman keeps the local sense of fear, night, or threshold alive without reducing it to one neat plotline. It draws attention to how people remember where not to go, what not to ignore, and how danger is pictured. The story's hold comes from recurring motifs of warning and boundary, not from boilerplate suspense. What remains is the feeling that certain edges of the world are never entirely empty."
    ],
    "zh": [
      "《飞翔的荷兰人》最好先放回西欧的荷兰的讲述传统里来理解。这条叙述把重心落在“警示”“边界”和“恐惧”这些意象上，而不是单一固定版本上。它更适合被读作关于“警示”“边界”“恐惧”的地方讲述。因此开头就把地点、社群和传承方式一起摆了出来。",
      "作为异兽传说，它最有力量的时候，是“警示”“边界”和“恐惧”一起把某片边界写得危险而有形。这种存在之所以重要，是因为它会让夜晚、河岸、树林或路口像真的住着什么东西。许多相关讲法本来就不是靠统一剧情活下来的，而是靠反复提醒与反复害怕。这也解释了为什么地点气氛常常比单一情节更关键。",
      "《飞翔的荷兰人》保存的是一种地方性的恐惧感，而不是被压成一段整齐的追逐故事。它提醒人们哪些地方不该轻忽，哪些界线不该随便跨过。真正让故事成立的是“警示”和“边界”这类反复出现的感受。最后留下来的，是某些世界边缘从来不会真正空无一物的感觉。"
    ]
  },
